FBIS4-53330 "dreas096_a_94026" FBIS-EAS-94-096 Daily Report 18 May 1994 NORTHEAST ASIA Japan Fujii Says Bond Revenue Goal May Be Hard To Achieve Fujii Says Bond Revenue Goal May Be Hard To Achieve OW1805045694 Tokyo KYODO in English 0414 GMT 18 May 94 OW1805045694 Tokyo KYODO English BFN [Text] Tokyo, May 18 KYODO -- Finance Minister Hirohisa Fujii said Wednesday [18 May] his ministry's goal of holding bond revenues to less than 5 percent of the government's general account budget in fiscal 1999 may be difficult to achieve. Fujii, answering questions before the Budget Committee of the House of Representatives, said the goal is a "target to strive for." The ministry published the goal in a medium-term fiscal outlook it submitted to the committee Tuesday.
